[_R. rickettsii_ has been isolated from dogs, opossums, and wild rabbits in
Brazil. It would be useful to study the molecular genetics of a Brazilian
strain of _R. ricketssii_, comparative studies such as are being done in
France (Zuzana Sekeyova, e-mail: coxiella@medecine.univ-mrs.fr) and at
CDC/Atlanta rur1@cdc.gov>.
I apologize for not being able to determine the particular person who sent
this message. Nonetheless, there should be more than enough information for
anyone who wants to contact one of the principal investigators. -- Mod CHC]
